# Sales mode

## Language bans (any file)
These words are banned — rewrite when you see them:
- synergy, synergize
- leverage (as a verb, used loosely)
- align / alignment (when used as fluff)
- reach out (prefer "email", "call", "ping")
- circle back
- thought leadership
- best-in-class

## Outbound message rules
- Message 1 ≤ 60 words.
- Every message has a specific (not generic) hook pulled from the prospect's site or LinkedIn.
- The ask in message 1 is a yes/no question, never a meeting request.
- No feature lists in message 1.

## Proposal rules
- Every paragraph must be traceable to a discovery note.
- If it wasn't discussed, it doesn't go in.
- Pricing appears once, anchored next to value, never as a price-only table.

## Pipeline hygiene
- Any deal without a next step + date is "stalled" — flag.
- Any deal >45 days with no movement is "killed" — close out, move on.
